1
00:00:05,701 --> 00:00:07,331
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,331 --> 00:00:09,101
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,001 --> 00:00:11,171
Is someone there?

4
00:00:11,231 --> 00:00:13,071
(Episode 17)

5
00:00:13,141 --> 00:00:14,341
Who's there?

6
00:00:16,241 --> 00:00:17,311
I swear I just...

7
00:00:17,911 --> 00:00:19,081
Who's behind...

8
00:00:20,641 --> 00:00:21,711
It's me.

9
00:00:36,061 --> 00:00:37,631
Where do you think you're going?

10
00:00:39,101 --> 00:00:40,101
You're awake?

11
00:00:41,801 --> 00:00:43,901
Sorry, I must have been exhausted.

12
00:00:45,171 --> 00:00:48,201
Thoughtless of me, wasn't it?
Insisting we watch a movie.

13
00:00:50,441 --> 00:00:51,941
I just woke up...

14
00:00:52,211 --> 00:00:55,111
and saw you right next to me.
Am I dreaming?

15
00:00:57,451 --> 00:00:58,651
What if I just moved in?

16
00:00:58,981 --> 00:01:01,251
I could just lie and say
I'm getting a roommate.

17
00:01:03,251 --> 00:01:06,191
You can't do that.
We need our parents' permission.

18
00:01:06,821 --> 00:01:08,731
You're such a stick-in-the-mud.

19
00:01:09,761 --> 00:01:11,291
Like they'll ever approve.

20
00:01:13,361 --> 00:01:17,001
I know our families' 30-year feud
won't just vanish overnight,

21
00:01:18,101 --> 00:01:21,141
but I'll slowly win them over
and get their blessing.

22
00:01:21,201 --> 00:01:22,211
Just trust me.

23
00:01:23,341 --> 00:01:25,911
Honestly, I'm not so sure.

24
00:01:27,441 --> 00:01:29,511
And I don't think
I can face your mother again.

25
00:01:32,451 --> 00:01:34,481
My stepmom... She's a good person.

26
00:01:34,551 --> 00:01:36,191
You'll see,
once you get to know her.

27
00:01:37,351 --> 00:01:40,491
But you never really lived
with your stepmother...

28
00:01:40,561 --> 00:01:42,861
or saw her much, did you?

29
00:01:43,961 --> 00:01:45,461
My stepmother...

30
00:01:45,931 --> 00:01:49,931
sent me an email every single week
I was studying abroad.

31
00:01:50,671 --> 00:01:52,371
Without missing a single one,

32
00:01:53,041 --> 00:01:56,071
an email would arrive
every Monday morning.

33
00:01:57,971 --> 00:02:01,981
She'd tell me about the family
and what happened during the week.

34
00:02:02,251 --> 00:02:04,081
Her emails were always long
and full of details.

35
00:02:05,951 --> 00:02:07,281
At first,

36
00:02:07,721 --> 00:02:09,591
I'd ignore them and never reply,
but...

37
00:02:10,691 --> 00:02:12,991
I began looking forward to Mondays.

38
00:02:12,991 --> 00:02:14,691
It made my week start
on a happier note.

39
00:02:16,691 --> 00:02:20,801
Whenever the seasons changed,
she'd send me new clothes and shoes.

40
00:02:21,131 --> 00:02:22,801
And for my birthday and Christmas,

41
00:02:23,131 --> 00:02:25,741
she'd always send a card
with a handwritten note.

42
00:02:25,871 --> 00:02:28,811
Wow, I'm touched just hearing that.

43
00:02:29,811 --> 00:02:31,511
She sounds like such a warm person.

44
00:02:32,111 --> 00:02:33,111
That's not even the half of it.

45
00:02:33,481 --> 00:02:37,251
Family events, cooking, housework...
Seriously,

46
00:02:37,311 --> 00:02:39,521
she's someone
who handles everything perfectly.

47
00:02:39,921 --> 00:02:40,921
Oh, my.

48
00:02:41,721 --> 00:02:43,921
That's kind of intimidating.

49
00:02:46,361 --> 00:02:50,491
You know what
I'm most grateful to my stepmom for?

50
00:02:53,001 --> 00:02:54,531
I had given up on my own family.

51
00:02:55,601 --> 00:02:57,871
I was so ashamed of them,

52
00:02:58,201 --> 00:02:59,701
but she was the one
who changed all that.

53
00:03:02,241 --> 00:03:06,011
She seems incredibly devoted
to the family.

54
00:03:07,011 --> 00:03:08,011
Totally.

55
00:03:09,381 --> 00:03:11,851
She's the type
who would do anything for family.

56
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:14,351
What should we do?

57
00:03:15,381 --> 00:03:18,121
If only we had a video of the fall.

58
00:03:21,121 --> 00:03:22,131
A video?

59
00:03:33,801 --> 00:03:34,801
You...

60
00:03:35,941 --> 00:03:37,441
You took a video of me, didn't you?

61
00:03:39,211 --> 00:03:41,741
No! Anything but that, honey.

62
00:03:42,211 --> 00:03:45,251
That's the most humiliating moment
of your entire life.

63
00:03:45,381 --> 00:03:48,381
I don't care, honey.
This is all for you.

64
00:03:48,481 --> 00:03:52,191
- So what if I'm a bit embarrassed?
- This is beyond embarrassing!

65
00:03:52,461 --> 00:03:55,221
Honey, this is utterly humiliating.

66
00:03:55,391 --> 00:03:56,791
The more humiliating it is,

67
00:03:56,791 --> 00:03:59,161
the guiltier
Dr. Gong will feel, right?

68
00:03:59,901 --> 00:04:00,961
You've got a point.

69
00:04:01,501 --> 00:04:03,271
That guy's too nice
for his own good.

70
00:04:05,431 --> 00:04:08,201
He'll feel so bad he has to agree
to be on the show, right?

71
00:04:09,771 --> 00:04:10,811
No!

72
00:04:11,171 --> 00:04:13,911
Yang Dong Ik,
what the heck are you thinking?

73
00:04:14,241 --> 00:04:17,451
No. This is wrong! No!

74
00:04:17,611 --> 00:04:19,081
What's gotten into you?

75
00:04:19,181 --> 00:04:21,781
If it gets you a seat
on the city council,

76
00:04:22,051 --> 00:04:23,391
I'd welcome even more humiliation.

77
00:04:25,121 --> 00:04:26,121
Right now,

78
00:04:27,091 --> 00:04:28,221
Se Ri, you really...

79
00:04:28,861 --> 00:04:30,531
Do you really love me this much?

80
00:04:31,361 --> 00:04:34,661
Give it here, quick. I'll post it
on the neighborhood forum.

81
00:04:34,861 --> 00:04:37,901
It'll just be a local embarrassment,
so don't worry, honey.

82
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:41,941
My Lord, please let this work.

83
00:04:50,011 --> 00:04:51,181
(Onjeong Police Substation)

84
00:04:53,051 --> 00:04:54,051
What's this?

85
00:04:59,391 --> 00:05:01,491
Isn't that Dr. Yang's wife...

86
00:05:01,761 --> 00:05:04,091
and Dr. Gong's eldest daughter?

87
00:05:08,231 --> 00:05:10,631
(Gong Ju Ah,
Head Designer at Taehan Group)

88
00:05:13,571 --> 00:05:14,571
(Taehan Group Designer Shoves
and Injures VIP Client)

89
00:05:14,571 --> 00:05:15,571
(Accident or Intentional?)

90
00:05:15,641 --> 00:05:17,411
Hey, what is this?

91
00:05:18,071 --> 00:05:22,011
Looks like this video was edited
to make the push look deliberate.

92
00:05:23,551 --> 00:05:26,651
Man, this is going to blow up.

93
00:05:26,851 --> 00:05:29,121
For crying out loud...

94
00:05:29,951 --> 00:05:33,591
It only has 100 views.
And there's hardly any reaction.

95
00:05:33,861 --> 00:05:36,031
You're right. I guess...

96
00:05:36,091 --> 00:05:37,931
I'll have to post it
on a bigger online forum.

97
00:05:41,031 --> 00:05:43,401
Here, this is for you, Grandpa.

98
00:05:44,001 --> 00:05:45,771
You made soup this early
in the morning?

99
00:05:46,071 --> 00:05:49,541
Of course. Mom isn't feeling well,
so I had to help out.

100
00:05:50,271 --> 00:05:53,381
My gosh, Father. Isn't our Eun Bin
just so thoughtful?

101
00:05:53,641 --> 00:05:56,781
She's such a great help.

102
00:05:59,281 --> 00:06:00,881
They're buying it, right?

103
00:06:01,621 --> 00:06:03,251
Don't forget my cut.

104
00:06:04,391 --> 00:06:07,321
A friend sent me a link
to a funny video,

105
00:06:07,461 --> 00:06:09,061
and the person who falls in it
looks like you, Auntie.

106
00:06:09,461 --> 00:06:10,831
What? Let me see.

107
00:06:12,261 --> 00:06:13,801
Is that video making the rounds?

108
00:06:14,101 --> 00:06:18,071
- Oh, no! What am I going to do?
- Hey, what is it? What's going on?

109
00:06:22,811 --> 00:06:24,511
(Gong Ju Ah,
Head Designer at Taehan Group)

110
00:06:26,741 --> 00:06:30,651
Gosh, how awful!
What on earth happened, Se Ri?

111
00:06:30,911 --> 00:06:34,981
Wow, total humiliation! I mean,
you took a really nasty spill.

112
00:06:35,321 --> 00:06:38,891
But they made Ju Ah
look like a total villain.

113
00:06:39,061 --> 00:06:40,391
What? What did you say?

114
00:06:40,991 --> 00:06:44,031
- Let me see it.
- Hey, wait, me too.

115
00:06:49,071 --> 00:06:50,531
(Taehan Group Designer Shoves
and Injures VIP Client)

116
00:06:50,531 --> 00:06:51,601
(Accident or Intentional?)

117
00:06:58,041 --> 00:07:02,851
Hey, Ji Hu. Where was this posted?

118
00:07:03,181 --> 00:07:05,681
It's a YouTube channel
that posts funny video compilations.

119
00:07:06,381 --> 00:07:08,121
It has over 100,000 subscribers.

120
00:07:09,391 --> 00:07:10,691
How did it end up on there?

121
00:07:11,221 --> 00:07:12,521
Have a lot of people seen it?

122
00:07:12,991 --> 00:07:15,791
- It has over 50,000 views.
- What? My gosh...

123
00:07:15,861 --> 00:07:16,861
Fifty thousand?

124
00:07:20,901 --> 00:07:22,401
Hello? Hyun Bin.

125
00:07:30,741 --> 00:07:32,611
So you've seen the video.

126
00:07:33,211 --> 00:07:34,481
It seems someone posted it for fun,

127
00:07:34,481 --> 00:07:36,811
and a YouTuber's share
made it viral.

128
00:07:37,381 --> 00:07:40,681
Our legal team will file
a takedown request immediately.

129
00:07:40,751 --> 00:07:44,391
We're forming a team to monitor it
so it doesn't spread further.

130
00:07:44,451 --> 00:07:45,821
So it'll be resolved soon.

131
00:07:46,391 --> 00:07:48,691
By the way, is my stepmother okay?

132
00:07:49,731 --> 00:07:51,091
I can't believe this!

133
00:07:51,431 --> 00:07:54,201
You must be too embarrassed to be
seen in the neighborhood, Se Ri.

134
00:07:54,661 --> 00:07:57,871
I know. Tomorrow, I have a meeting
with the other doctors' wives.

135
00:07:58,531 --> 00:08:01,241
Today, you and I were supposed
to go look at a storefront.

136
00:08:01,601 --> 00:08:05,611
Se Ri, is that your real worry?
Do not leave the house, okay?

137
00:08:05,711 --> 00:08:08,181
- What's this ruckus? Let me see!
- Father!

138
00:08:08,241 --> 00:08:09,251
- No!
- No, you can't!

139
00:08:09,681 --> 00:08:13,181
Oh, please don't look, Father.
If you see it too,

140
00:08:13,551 --> 00:08:16,051
I'll just die of embarrassment.

141
00:08:16,791 --> 00:08:17,851
Hyun Bin says...

142
00:08:18,191 --> 00:08:19,661
the company is taking care of it
quickly.

143
00:08:20,621 --> 00:08:24,231
Goodness, but the witch hunt
in the comments is insane.

144
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:27,461
Everyone's making a fuss, saying
Ju Ah pushed Mom intentionally.

145
00:08:28,161 --> 00:08:30,431
"Looks like Taehan hires thugs,
not designers."

146
00:08:30,701 --> 00:08:33,271
"One employee is tanking
Taehan's entire image."

147
00:08:34,841 --> 00:08:37,971
There are news articles out now too.
Man, Ju Ah is so getting fired.

148
00:08:38,171 --> 00:08:39,911
My gosh,
what's going to happen to her?

149
00:08:48,481 --> 00:08:49,991
The HR team at the head office...

150
00:08:50,491 --> 00:08:52,461
has decided to call
a disciplinary hearing.

151
00:08:53,561 --> 00:08:54,561
Disciplinary hearing?

152
00:08:56,731 --> 00:08:59,031
Now that the video has become
a news story,

153
00:08:59,661 --> 00:09:01,731
they're just taking
the necessary measures.

154
00:09:03,171 --> 00:09:04,701
We're not going to blame this
on you.

155
00:09:05,001 --> 00:09:08,141
We'll present it as an issue caused
by an insufficient event manual.

156
00:09:08,801 --> 00:09:12,641
So at the hearing,
I just need to explain...

157
00:09:12,711 --> 00:09:14,781
what happened. Is that right?

158
00:09:15,111 --> 00:09:19,151
Yes. Prepare your statement.
At home.

159
00:09:19,881 --> 00:09:20,881
Take your time.

160
00:09:22,221 --> 00:09:23,521
- At home?
- Well...

161
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:26,691
You're suspended until the hearing.

162
00:09:35,061 --> 00:09:37,631
Lucky you.
You haven't had a break in a while.

163
00:09:38,931 --> 00:09:41,671
Right, I should try to overcome
this tragic situation...

164
00:09:41,741 --> 00:09:44,041
with an optimistic mindset.

165
00:09:45,371 --> 00:09:46,541
Hey, this won't...

166
00:09:46,541 --> 00:09:49,211
jeopardize our deal with
Hyegyeong Department Store, right?

167
00:09:49,311 --> 00:09:50,811
Of course not.

168
00:09:50,911 --> 00:09:53,021
Hyegyeong's people
were at the event.

169
00:09:53,081 --> 00:09:56,951
They saw him shank the shot.
They know what happened. It's fine.

170
00:09:59,221 --> 00:10:01,121
Is this Director Baek's doing?

171
00:10:01,391 --> 00:10:04,291
Yes. He's dragging it out
with a probe.

172
00:10:04,361 --> 00:10:05,531
He's poisoning the mood
in the company.

173
00:10:05,901 --> 00:10:08,331
He also wants to damage
our division's reputation.

174
00:10:09,401 --> 00:10:12,471
Even so,
calling a disciplinary hearing...

175
00:10:12,471 --> 00:10:13,841
before anything is resolved?

176
00:10:13,941 --> 00:10:16,241
Doesn't that seem unreasonable
and make his motives obvious?

177
00:10:18,471 --> 00:10:21,041
I never should have invited
your parents.

178
00:10:21,881 --> 00:10:23,381
I've just made things awkward
for a lot of people.

179
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:26,521
- I'm sorry.
- Good. As long as you know.

180
00:10:28,221 --> 00:10:32,121
If I find the original poster,
just watch. I won't let it slide.

181
00:10:33,561 --> 00:10:34,891
I'll destroy them.

182
00:10:41,301 --> 00:10:43,031
Who the heck would do
something like that?

183
00:10:44,201 --> 00:10:48,201
What if Hyun Bin's company finds
the person who posted the video?

184
00:10:48,771 --> 00:10:51,411
It won't take them long to find out
we were the ones who posted it.

185
00:10:51,971 --> 00:10:54,281
Should I just come clean
to Hyun Bin now?

186
00:10:54,841 --> 00:10:57,451
No. Since it's come to this,

187
00:10:57,951 --> 00:10:59,881
we have no choice
but to see it through, honey.

188
00:11:00,521 --> 00:11:01,981
You need to be strong.

189
00:11:02,481 --> 00:11:04,791
You're the one
who needs to be strong.

190
00:11:05,091 --> 00:11:07,361
They say tens of thousands of people
have seen it. What should we do?

191
00:11:07,561 --> 00:11:08,761
I'm Cha Se Ri.

192
00:11:09,061 --> 00:11:11,661
You really think I can't handle
a little thing like this for you?

193
00:11:12,391 --> 00:11:16,471
But it seems Jeong Han's daughter
will be in trouble too. What now?

194
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:18,331
I know.

195
00:11:19,031 --> 00:11:21,201
Gosh, I had no idea
it would blow up like this.

196
00:11:31,651 --> 00:11:32,651
What are you doing?

197
00:11:32,821 --> 00:11:36,651
These punks are calling our Ju Ah
a witch.

198
00:11:36,891 --> 00:11:38,251
So I'm going to leave
a comment myself.

199
00:11:38,791 --> 00:11:40,221
"Don't you dare run your mouths."

200
00:11:40,821 --> 00:11:45,461
It's a scary world. How can someone
edit and spread something so vile?

201
00:11:45,731 --> 00:11:47,761
That's what
these online clout chasers do.

202
00:11:48,001 --> 00:11:52,171
They make clickbait for views
and pump out tons of fake news.

203
00:11:52,531 --> 00:11:56,911
We were worried this would happen.
That's why the company was strict.

204
00:11:57,211 --> 00:12:00,111
So, who on earth
could have leaked this video?

205
00:12:00,281 --> 00:12:03,081
I think this is why Dr. Yang
missed morning exercise.

206
00:12:03,251 --> 00:12:05,751
A lot of people were watching it
during exercise earlier.

207
00:12:06,581 --> 00:12:10,191
The gossip must be all over
the neighborhood and market by now.

208
00:12:10,551 --> 00:12:11,721
Oh, for crying out loud.

209
00:12:12,621 --> 00:12:15,021
Mom, have you heard back
from Ju Ah yet?

210
00:12:15,461 --> 00:12:19,601
No. She's at work,
so I don't want to bother her.

211
00:12:20,931 --> 00:12:22,671
What? My gosh, what's this?

212
00:12:23,431 --> 00:12:25,131
Hey, the video's gone.
I was in the middle of a comment.

213
00:12:25,601 --> 00:12:26,871
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

214
00:12:26,941 --> 00:12:29,971
That's a relief. I guess
the company is taking care of it.

215
00:12:31,211 --> 00:12:32,511
Oh, it's Ju Ah.

216
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:34,341
- My gosh.
- Here.

217
00:12:35,741 --> 00:12:36,981
Hi, Ju Ah.

218
00:12:37,851 --> 00:12:38,851
Are you okay?

219
00:12:39,351 --> 00:12:43,191
Of course, Grandma.
The company took care of everything.

220
00:12:43,691 --> 00:12:47,291
This is a major company.
The video's probably already down.

221
00:12:50,031 --> 00:12:54,501
- Yes, right.
- Grandma, tell Dad not to worry.

222
00:12:55,001 --> 00:12:57,701
I have to go to a meeting now,
so I'll talk to you later.

223
00:12:58,031 --> 00:12:59,031
Okay.

224
00:13:01,171 --> 00:13:03,571
Right, okay. I understand. Yes.

225
00:13:14,551 --> 00:13:15,881
Is your family worried?

226
00:13:16,451 --> 00:13:18,621
I reassured them that I'm fine.

227
00:13:20,221 --> 00:13:21,321
Good.

228
00:13:21,621 --> 00:13:23,291
We got the articles and the video
taken down,

229
00:13:23,361 --> 00:13:26,201
but it'll take a while to remove
what was shared by individuals.

230
00:13:27,631 --> 00:13:31,371
I'm prepared for it,
so don't worry about me, Director.

231
00:13:32,501 --> 00:13:34,241
You're as tough as ever, Gong Ju Ah.

232
00:13:35,901 --> 00:13:36,911
Yes.

233
00:13:43,151 --> 00:13:45,311
Why go so far as to suspend her?

234
00:13:45,311 --> 00:13:47,221
Director Yang's mom
wasn't even hurt.

235
00:13:49,391 --> 00:13:51,321
Wait, the woman who fell
was Director Yang's mother?

236
00:14:01,261 --> 00:14:02,261
Did you hear?

237
00:14:02,601 --> 00:14:05,871
I heard the VIP Ms. Gong pushed
was Director Yang's mother.

238
00:14:06,401 --> 00:14:07,401
Really?

239
00:14:08,071 --> 00:14:10,141
But doesn't Ms. Gong work
in Director Yang's office?

240
00:14:10,471 --> 00:14:14,881
Exactly. I hear they don't get along
and are always fighting.

241
00:14:15,481 --> 00:14:18,251
Still, you don't think she'd push
her boss' mom over that, do you?

242
00:14:18,451 --> 00:14:20,121
That's why she's being disciplined.

243
00:14:20,381 --> 00:14:21,751
She has a crazy temper, you know.

244
00:14:38,871 --> 00:14:39,871
Yes.

245
00:14:42,841 --> 00:14:45,041
What a surprise.
What brings you here?

246
00:14:45,371 --> 00:14:47,711
Why? Can't I visit my mom
at her clinic?

247
00:14:48,141 --> 00:14:51,011
- So, what is it?
- I came to treat you to a meal.

248
00:14:51,251 --> 00:14:54,881
- All of a sudden?
- You're our exclusive model.

249
00:14:55,181 --> 00:14:58,251
As your designer,
I'm here to go over the schedule.

250
00:14:58,321 --> 00:15:00,621
I heard you were put
on home suspension.

251
00:15:00,991 --> 00:15:02,521
Director Yang called me.

252
00:15:03,461 --> 00:15:07,831
Too embarrassed to go home,
and with nowhere else to go.

253
00:15:09,001 --> 00:15:12,071
And when that happens,
you can only go to your mom, right?

254
00:15:13,271 --> 00:15:14,941
You're impossible, really.

255
00:15:17,241 --> 00:15:18,311
Let's go.

256
00:15:30,151 --> 00:15:31,291
Do you eat lunch alone?

257
00:15:32,821 --> 00:15:35,091
Sometimes I do, sometimes I don't.

258
00:15:35,591 --> 00:15:37,531
If you sometimes eat alone,

259
00:15:37,531 --> 00:15:40,001
you should give me a call.
I'm right nearby.

260
00:15:40,131 --> 00:15:42,631
We always fight when we're together.
What's the point?

261
00:15:43,031 --> 00:15:44,401
You're exhausting to be around.

262
00:15:57,311 --> 00:15:59,251
Go ahead and act like that
in front of your boyfriend.

263
00:15:59,581 --> 00:16:00,781
I'm sure he'd really love that.

264
00:16:01,021 --> 00:16:03,091
Then I'll just find someone
who likes me for who I am.

265
00:16:03,221 --> 00:16:07,121
Even if you're madly in love,
you'll notice turnoffs.

266
00:16:07,321 --> 00:16:09,091
I've heard that for many couples,

267
00:16:09,091 --> 00:16:11,091
the first turnoff is often
the way their partner eats.

268
00:16:11,461 --> 00:16:15,101
So, at least try
to have some table manners.

269
00:16:15,731 --> 00:16:19,471
I can't even eat in peace.
You know I'm here because I'm upset.

270
00:16:22,001 --> 00:16:23,441
How many days is your suspension?

271
00:16:23,811 --> 00:16:26,071
Three days.
They want a written statement.

272
00:16:27,141 --> 00:16:30,081
Why do you have to write one?
What did you do wrong?

273
00:16:30,511 --> 00:16:33,981
Everyone knows it was an accident,
and the CCTV should prove it.

274
00:16:34,181 --> 00:16:37,051
Of course, I know that.
But it's all over the news now,

275
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,491
so they're just doing this
for formality.

276
00:16:45,761 --> 00:16:49,901
Just say it.
Stop giving me that pathetic look.

277
00:16:51,131 --> 00:16:52,201
Go pay the bill.

278
00:16:55,071 --> 00:16:58,611
We just don't click.
We're like oil and water.

279
00:16:59,911 --> 00:17:01,181
Goodness, seriously.

280
00:17:01,711 --> 00:17:05,451
Tell Kim Seong Jun to get tested,
and then I'll see him.

281
00:17:06,111 --> 00:17:08,251
Yes. My daughter's here
for a rare visit,

282
00:17:08,251 --> 00:17:09,851
so I'll spend some time with her.

283
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:11,821
Okay.

284
00:17:16,221 --> 00:17:18,361
Hey, let's take a walk.
It'll help with digestion.

285
00:17:18,591 --> 00:17:22,161
- Aren't you busy?
- No. I'm free until 3 p.m.

286
00:17:22,731 --> 00:17:24,071
Consider yourself lucky.

287
00:17:42,751 --> 00:17:44,551
How come you're not telling me
to quit this time?

288
00:17:45,351 --> 00:17:48,221
Tell me to quit everything
and become a doctor.

289
00:17:49,631 --> 00:17:51,291
You wouldn't quit anyway.

290
00:17:52,491 --> 00:17:53,661
Go on, nag me.

291
00:17:54,201 --> 00:17:56,331
I'm ready for it.

292
00:17:58,931 --> 00:18:02,571
I got married as a college sophomore
with nothing to my name.

293
00:18:04,841 --> 00:18:09,011
Are you bragging about that?
So reckless for a college sophomore.

294
00:18:09,441 --> 00:18:10,451
Tell me about it.

295
00:18:12,051 --> 00:18:14,381
I had no parents, no siblings...

296
00:18:14,451 --> 00:18:17,521
The only thing I had in the world
was you in my belly.

297
00:18:19,251 --> 00:18:23,461
Back then, your father was my haven
in my lonely life.

298
00:18:24,891 --> 00:18:28,801
What? You said you would never have
married Dad if it weren't for me.

299
00:18:29,101 --> 00:18:33,041
You've been singing that same tune
about having to marry him for me.

300
00:18:33,941 --> 00:18:34,941
That's right.

301
00:18:35,541 --> 00:18:37,041
If it weren't for you,

302
00:18:37,041 --> 00:18:39,611
I'd have been too ashamed
to marry into the Gong family.

303
00:18:40,581 --> 00:18:42,141
Because I was pregnant with you,

304
00:18:42,511 --> 00:18:44,951
I just went for it, even though
I felt like I wasn't good enough.

305
00:18:46,851 --> 00:18:48,151
Think about it.

306
00:18:48,381 --> 00:18:52,491
A family of doctors...
Did you think they'd ever accept me?

307
00:18:53,621 --> 00:18:56,121
All I ever knew how to do was study.

308
00:18:57,491 --> 00:18:59,701
I was terrible at housekeeping
and raising children.

309
00:19:01,431 --> 00:19:02,831
But despite all that,

310
00:19:03,671 --> 00:19:07,141
they accepted and cared for me
like I was their own daughter.

311
00:19:09,241 --> 00:19:12,471
To the people who took in someone
as worthless as me,

312
00:19:12,971 --> 00:19:16,911
I wondered how I could ever live
to repay their kindness.

313
00:19:19,281 --> 00:19:21,781
So I thought,
"I'll become a great doctor."

314
00:19:22,881 --> 00:19:25,121
"And I'll raise my children
to be doctors, too."

315
00:19:26,321 --> 00:19:28,621
Since the only thing I passed to you
was my brain,

316
00:19:28,961 --> 00:19:30,861
I figured you'd at least be good
at studying.

317
00:19:33,501 --> 00:19:34,801
That's why I was like that.

318
00:19:37,371 --> 00:19:38,931
I admit it was
my own selfish ambition.

319
00:19:41,301 --> 00:19:42,741
At least you admit it.

320
00:19:45,711 --> 00:19:49,481
Honestly, until recently,
I thought you were being spiteful...

321
00:19:49,541 --> 00:19:52,111
and that you quit medicine
out of some childish rebellion.

322
00:19:53,151 --> 00:19:54,151
But?

323
00:19:56,321 --> 00:19:59,151
On the day Director Yang came
to offer me the contract,

324
00:20:00,661 --> 00:20:01,921
I let it all go.

325
00:20:03,161 --> 00:20:04,991
The reason you became a designer...

326
00:20:05,961 --> 00:20:07,501
That's when I finally understood.

327
00:20:11,931 --> 00:20:15,971
At the event, standing by your dad,
wearing the clothes you made...

328
00:20:16,541 --> 00:20:17,611
I was so proud.

329
00:20:21,481 --> 00:20:23,511
So stick it out and win.

330
00:20:23,951 --> 00:20:25,881
Don't just whine about
how hard things are.

331
00:20:26,551 --> 00:20:29,481
You're doing what you love.
What's a little trouble like this?

332
00:20:32,591 --> 00:20:33,621
Right.

333
00:20:45,171 --> 00:20:49,341
I'm so impressed.
You're making mille-feuille nabe.

334
00:20:49,701 --> 00:20:52,611
Make sure you tell
Grandpa and Dad, okay?

335
00:20:53,611 --> 00:20:56,651
- You're making dinner already?
- Yes, she has plans.

336
00:20:56,911 --> 00:20:59,511
But are you sure you'll be okay
checking out the shop alone?

337
00:21:00,251 --> 00:21:03,951
I'm fine, but you must be frustrated
being stuck at home.

338
00:21:04,491 --> 00:21:07,921
Even if you feel cooped up,
don't go out. I went to the market,

339
00:21:07,991 --> 00:21:10,631
and the whole neighborhood
was talking about you, Mom.

340
00:21:11,231 --> 00:21:12,631
What are we going to do?

341
00:21:13,091 --> 00:21:16,701
It's okay. I looked pretty graceful
when I fell, you know.

342
00:21:17,731 --> 00:21:19,941
Right, it's good that
you're seeing the glass half full.

343
00:21:19,941 --> 00:21:21,941
- See you.
- Wait, Dong Suk.

344
00:21:22,741 --> 00:21:26,211
Weren't you checking out the store
at 7 p.m.? You're leaving already?

345
00:21:26,211 --> 00:21:29,181
What? Oh, well...

346
00:21:29,381 --> 00:21:31,151
I was going to stop by
the hair salon on my way.

347
00:21:31,151 --> 00:21:32,151
See you later!

348
00:21:33,681 --> 00:21:36,281
Do you think
she's really going to the shop?

349
00:21:36,351 --> 00:21:39,791
It looks more like
she's going on a date.

350
00:21:39,921 --> 00:21:41,521
Hey, do you know something I don't?

351
00:21:41,921 --> 00:21:43,891
It's some guy from the neighborhood.
I overheard her phone call.

352
00:21:44,191 --> 00:21:46,931
So, she went to a motel
with someone from the neighborhood?

353
00:21:46,931 --> 00:21:48,031
She went to a motel?

354
00:21:48,901 --> 00:21:49,901
Keep your voice down.

355
00:21:50,771 --> 00:21:52,931
Anyway, who are you off to meet?

356
00:21:53,301 --> 00:21:55,571
It's not Dr. Gong's son, is it?

357
00:21:55,671 --> 00:21:59,311
No, I'd never worry you like that.
I'm meeting someone else.

358
00:22:00,481 --> 00:22:01,481
Who?

359
00:22:06,111 --> 00:22:08,121
What's taking him so long?
I'm freezing to death out here.

360
00:22:08,881 --> 00:22:11,891
(Full Preparation for All Subjects
at Jeonghu Academy)

361
00:22:12,821 --> 00:22:14,221
Eun Bin?
Don't tell me you came here for me.

362
00:22:14,361 --> 00:22:17,791
Yes. For my dear Ji Hu,
who's bummed about his grades.

363
00:22:17,861 --> 00:22:19,631
I came to treat you
to something good.

364
00:22:20,001 --> 00:22:23,531
- What's the catch?
- Just be quiet and follow me, okay?

365
00:22:23,831 --> 00:22:28,401
I'm treating you to a power meal.
All right?

366
00:22:29,371 --> 00:22:31,071
If you're excited,
let me hear you scream!

367
00:22:32,241 --> 00:22:34,841
(Damga Charcoal Grill,
Onjeong Market)

368
00:22:38,911 --> 00:22:41,851
It tastes so much better
because you're grilling it.

369
00:22:42,181 --> 00:22:44,121
You haven't even had
a single bite yet.

370
00:22:45,991 --> 00:22:46,991
Here you go.

371
00:22:48,891 --> 00:22:51,161
- Eat up.
- Thanks.

372
00:22:53,061 --> 00:22:56,131
I knew it. You were too embarrassed
to come alone, so you brought me.

373
00:22:56,231 --> 00:22:59,201
This kills 2 birds with 1 stone.
Now, hurry up and eat.

374
00:23:02,671 --> 00:23:05,011
- Oh, no. I'm so sorry.
- Are you okay?

375
00:23:05,141 --> 00:23:07,181
- Yes, I'm fine.
- Where...

376
00:23:07,241 --> 00:23:08,381
Just over there...

377
00:23:09,481 --> 00:23:11,381
Hey, be honest with me.

378
00:23:11,451 --> 00:23:14,351
What? You want to know
who I think is prettier, you or her?

379
00:23:14,481 --> 00:23:16,921
Yes. And don't say it's me
just because we're family.

380
00:23:16,991 --> 00:23:18,491
Just give me the objective facts.

381
00:23:18,551 --> 00:23:22,861
She's way better, obviously.
She's prettier and younger than you,

382
00:23:23,021 --> 00:23:25,161
and she has a similar vibe to him.

383
00:23:25,231 --> 00:23:26,261
They're a way better match.

384
00:23:26,631 --> 00:23:27,631
That's it, no more for you.

385
00:23:31,401 --> 00:23:32,401
Hi.

386
00:23:33,271 --> 00:23:37,271
Yes. Hi.
You're Woo Jae's girlfriend, right?

387
00:23:38,241 --> 00:23:40,311
Yes, that's right.
I'm his girlfriend.

388
00:23:41,011 --> 00:23:43,241
- So you do remember me.
- Yes.

389
00:23:43,311 --> 00:23:46,381
- She just has a huge crush on him.
- Hey!

390
00:23:46,381 --> 00:23:47,681
Oh, I see.

391
00:23:48,121 --> 00:23:49,181
Enjoy your meal.

392
00:23:50,191 --> 00:23:54,221
Excuse me,
have we met somewhere before?

393
00:23:55,961 --> 00:23:56,961
I don't think so.

394
00:23:58,061 --> 00:24:01,461
- Have you ever been to Baltimore?
- I'm sorry? Bal... What?

395
00:24:01,831 --> 00:24:04,571
I live there, actually.
I'm just visiting Korea briefly.

396
00:24:06,171 --> 00:24:07,801
I must have been mistaken.

397
00:24:08,871 --> 00:24:09,901
Enjoy your meal.

398
00:24:11,611 --> 00:24:15,311
- Do you know where Baltimore is?
- Whatever, you little brat.

399
00:24:15,881 --> 00:24:18,811
Who are you to tell her
that I have a crush on him?

400
00:24:19,011 --> 00:24:21,651
I'm just trying to keep the peace
between our families.

401
00:24:22,121 --> 00:24:24,491
Just think about
his family and ours.

402
00:24:24,721 --> 00:24:27,261
- As if a kid like you would know.
- What don't I know?

403
00:24:27,521 --> 00:24:30,131
I know why our two families
were enemies for 30 years,

404
00:24:30,391 --> 00:24:32,191
and I know who my dad
had an affair with.

405
00:24:32,691 --> 00:24:33,701
Am I missing anything?

406
00:24:34,231 --> 00:24:36,531
I can't even argue
since you're right.

407
00:24:36,901 --> 00:24:39,401
You can't be with that guy.
Don't break your mom's heart.

408
00:24:39,471 --> 00:24:41,471
- I'm going to be watching you.
- Hey!

409
00:24:41,901 --> 00:24:44,441
- Just shut your mouth and eat.
- How can I eat with my mouth shut?

410
00:24:44,511 --> 00:24:45,541
Figure it out.

411
00:24:53,581 --> 00:24:56,991
It could be a thyroid issue,
so let's start with a blood test.

412
00:24:57,421 --> 00:24:59,851
But wait, you said you've been dizzy
for two weeks straight.

413
00:24:59,921 --> 00:25:01,921
Why did you wait so long to come in?

414
00:25:02,191 --> 00:25:04,061
I had something I wanted to ask,

415
00:25:04,161 --> 00:25:06,391
so I came in
to kill 2 birds with 1 stone.

416
00:25:07,061 --> 00:25:11,231
What are you curious about now?
If Ju Ah pushed her on purpose?

417
00:25:11,301 --> 00:25:14,401
- Is that what you're wondering?
- She pushed her on purpose, right?

418
00:25:15,401 --> 00:25:17,171
It's the talk of the town.

419
00:25:18,041 --> 00:25:20,541
Ma'am, our Ju Ah
would never do that.

420
00:25:20,781 --> 00:25:23,041
This is ridiculous.
I'll go to the Merchants' Hall...

421
00:25:23,041 --> 00:25:25,011
to make an announcement
and clear this up.

422
00:25:25,111 --> 00:25:29,021
It's just that your two families
have such a bad history.

423
00:25:29,081 --> 00:25:30,821
I just thought it was a possibility.

424
00:25:31,151 --> 00:25:34,891
Ma'am, the things you say.

425
00:25:35,261 --> 00:25:37,431
That was more than 30 years ago.

426
00:25:37,431 --> 00:25:39,631
Even I've moved on,
so you should too.

427
00:25:39,991 --> 00:25:42,961
If we were still on bad terms,
would we live opposite each other?

428
00:25:43,431 --> 00:25:46,371
Yes, they get along fine as
the association's president and VP.

429
00:25:46,431 --> 00:25:47,941
Why is everyone making a big deal?
Honestly.

430
00:25:48,401 --> 00:25:51,111
You're right. Listen to me,
saying all sorts of nonsense.

431
00:25:51,771 --> 00:25:53,111
I'm sorry.

432
00:25:53,881 --> 00:25:57,711
- Gosh, I'll go for my blood test.
- Yes, of course. Please escort her.

433
00:25:57,781 --> 00:25:58,781
This way, please.

434
00:26:02,381 --> 00:26:04,291
You need to go over
to their clinic and apologize.

435
00:26:04,921 --> 00:26:06,861
This must be even harder for them.

436
00:26:07,221 --> 00:26:10,861
I was planning on it,
but I'm swamped with patients today.

437
00:26:11,831 --> 00:26:14,761
I'm going to the Merchants' Hall
after this. Want to come along?

438
00:26:14,831 --> 00:26:15,831
Me?

439
00:26:16,261 --> 00:26:19,531
No, I have plans today.
You take care of the apology.

440
00:26:19,701 --> 00:26:23,071
- What plans?
- Just plans.

441
00:26:23,841 --> 00:26:24,841
Plans.

442
00:26:26,271 --> 00:26:28,711
What... What's gotten into him?

443
00:26:37,721 --> 00:26:38,991
- Dong Suk...
- Oh, Mr. Gong.

444
00:26:39,151 --> 00:26:40,661
- Hey.
- What brings you here?

445
00:26:40,821 --> 00:26:43,021
I just had dinner and thought
I'd get some exercise.

446
00:26:43,091 --> 00:26:45,791
- Oh, exercise, that's great.
- Yes. You have a good one.

447
00:26:45,861 --> 00:26:47,761
- All right, take care.
- Yes, you too.

448
00:26:47,831 --> 00:26:48,831
Bye.

449
00:27:02,211 --> 00:27:04,451
I came here once with the realtor.

450
00:27:04,551 --> 00:27:06,711
They do well,
and the key money is low.

451
00:27:09,481 --> 00:27:11,591
Why would a place with good business
be listed for cheap?

452
00:27:12,351 --> 00:27:13,351
Really?

453
00:27:15,961 --> 00:27:19,391
Now that I look, I see
far fewer customers than before.

454
00:27:22,861 --> 00:27:24,731
If they know someone's coming
to check out the business,

455
00:27:25,901 --> 00:27:28,641
they'll plant fake customers
to make it look busy. Just packed.

456
00:27:28,641 --> 00:27:31,771
Seriously? So they're just trying
to unload the place quickly.

457
00:27:33,071 --> 00:27:34,711
I'm so glad you came with me.

458
00:27:38,211 --> 00:27:39,651
Dong Suk, are you a good cook?

459
00:27:40,621 --> 00:27:42,981
I used to be,
but I'm a little rusty.

460
00:27:43,381 --> 00:27:47,861
Besides, I'm only doing this because
my dad suddenly told me I should.

461
00:27:48,061 --> 00:27:50,631
- Then what about a franchise?
- A franchise?

462
00:27:50,691 --> 00:27:54,501
For a first-time owner like you,
it could be a lot easier.

463
00:27:57,231 --> 00:28:00,471
I'm impressionable. Now you say it,
that makes a lot of sense.

464
00:28:01,501 --> 00:28:02,701
I'll look into it
a little more for you.

465
00:28:03,071 --> 00:28:05,641
Thanks. For now,
let's just enjoy our food.

466
00:28:06,941 --> 00:28:09,611
Here, try some of this kimchi stew.
This looks delicious.

467
00:28:10,411 --> 00:28:11,511
It looks so good.

468
00:28:14,681 --> 00:28:17,251
- It's delicious.
- Oh, hey.

469
00:28:17,251 --> 00:28:18,791
How's your sister-in-law doing?

470
00:28:18,991 --> 00:28:20,261
She's just holed up at home.

471
00:28:20,721 --> 00:28:24,691
- Thousands saw her take that fall.
- Right. Oh, boy.

472
00:28:26,261 --> 00:28:29,361
But thanks to that, I got to
come with you today, you know?

473
00:28:30,001 --> 00:28:31,001
I guess so?

474
00:28:31,771 --> 00:28:33,901
How's your niece?
She must be stressed too.

475
00:28:33,901 --> 00:28:35,101
Yes, totally.

476
00:28:36,641 --> 00:28:39,271
It's not like my Ju Ah pushed her
on purpose or anything.

477
00:28:40,381 --> 00:28:43,581
But she could have pushed her
on purpose, right?

478
00:28:45,251 --> 00:28:46,251
Why?

479
00:28:46,911 --> 00:28:48,821
Why would my Ju Ah push someone
on purpose?

480
00:28:49,581 --> 00:28:53,591
Because my sister-in-law hit
your sister-in-law before.

481
00:28:54,861 --> 00:28:57,491
What? So you're saying my Ju Ah
was getting revenge for that?

482
00:28:58,191 --> 00:29:00,861
Dong Suk, I didn't raise Ju Ah
to be like that.

483
00:29:01,261 --> 00:29:04,771
Ju Ah was only trying
to protect her. Get it?

484
00:29:05,371 --> 00:29:08,471
Of course, you're going to take
your niece's side.

485
00:29:09,071 --> 00:29:11,341
You have a really twisted way
of putting things.

486
00:29:11,741 --> 00:29:14,241
Fine. I get it, okay?
Let's just eat.

487
00:29:14,311 --> 00:29:17,681
"Let's just eat?" Forget it!
No, we need to clear this up.

488
00:29:17,881 --> 00:29:21,251
About your sister-in-law
being humiliated,

489
00:29:21,321 --> 00:29:23,451
I feel terrible about it.

490
00:29:23,721 --> 00:29:26,651
My brother wasn't directly at fault,
but he's going to apologize.

491
00:29:26,991 --> 00:29:29,021
And besides, because of all this,
my Ju Ah...

492
00:29:29,091 --> 00:29:33,091
has taken a ton of heat for it.
Technically, we're the victims too.

493
00:29:34,161 --> 00:29:35,961
What do you mean you're the victims?

494
00:29:36,931 --> 00:29:41,541
Your brother mishit the ball.
If anyone's to blame, it's him.

495
00:29:41,601 --> 00:29:44,771
Look at you. Listen to yourself.
In what way is he to blame?

496
00:29:44,841 --> 00:29:47,011
Let's say you have a ball here.
You swing your club and hit it.

497
00:29:47,081 --> 00:29:49,941
Does the ball fly perfectly straight
where you want it? Does it for you?

498
00:29:50,011 --> 00:29:52,581
Goodness, forget it.
Did we come here to fight?

499
00:29:52,881 --> 00:29:53,981
Why are you picking a fight
over this?

500
00:29:54,051 --> 00:29:56,851
- What? You're picking a fight!
- Fine.

501
00:29:57,121 --> 00:29:58,621
I get it, so just drop it.

502
00:29:58,691 --> 00:30:00,891
Why are you telling me to drop it?
You're the one bringing it up.

503
00:30:01,361 --> 00:30:03,621
Goodness, forget it!
I must have been crazy.

504
00:30:04,591 --> 00:30:06,191
I should've known better
than to hang out with you.

505
00:30:08,931 --> 00:30:12,301
- Hey!
- Never contact me again, you hear?

506
00:30:13,401 --> 00:30:15,271
Hey, Dong Suk! Hey!

507
00:30:17,671 --> 00:30:20,171
Goodness, my pride's too hurt
to go chasing after her.

508
00:30:26,081 --> 00:30:28,451
- Can I get a bottle of soju?
- Sure.

509
00:30:30,521 --> 00:30:32,821
Yes, I'm just about to
leave the office, Stepmother.

510
00:30:33,391 --> 00:30:35,561
I have something for you,
so I'll head over to Onjeong.

511
00:30:35,921 --> 00:30:39,691
What perfect timing.
Eun Bin made something delicious.

512
00:30:41,231 --> 00:30:42,461
You must have had a rough day.

513
00:30:44,001 --> 00:30:47,841
It's just embarrassing,
being so publicly humiliated.

514
00:30:48,501 --> 00:30:52,241
And it's frustrating to cancel plans
and just stay cooped up at home.

515
00:30:53,171 --> 00:30:57,711
I'll find out who posted this video.
I won't let them get away with it.

516
00:30:58,411 --> 00:31:01,581
No! Don't do that. Son, I'm okay.

517
00:31:02,181 --> 00:31:06,391
I can take it,
but we can't go getting revenge.

518
00:31:06,591 --> 00:31:10,661
Besides, they're probably a VIP.
We should just let it go.

519
00:31:10,761 --> 00:31:12,161
I'm all right, so it doesn't matter.

520
00:31:12,831 --> 00:31:15,501
Gosh, if this unnecessarily hurts
the company's reputation,

521
00:31:15,801 --> 00:31:17,901
it will only make things harder
for my son, right?

522
00:31:19,601 --> 00:31:21,171
I understand what you're saying.

523
00:31:21,801 --> 00:31:24,171
You're always so big-hearted.

524
00:31:26,071 --> 00:31:27,311
Well, right.

525
00:31:27,681 --> 00:31:29,281
And what about Ms. Gong?

526
00:31:30,081 --> 00:31:32,111
Ms. Gong hasn't had trouble at work,
has she?

527
00:31:33,281 --> 00:31:34,281
What?

528
00:31:34,821 --> 00:31:35,821
What? Disciplinary action?

529
00:31:36,381 --> 00:31:38,791
No,
do they really need to go that far?

530
00:31:39,721 --> 00:31:40,891
I see.

531
00:31:41,191 --> 00:31:45,461
Okay, right. I get it.
Drive safe, okay?

532
00:31:48,331 --> 00:31:50,401
Disciplinary action? Seriously?

533
00:31:52,201 --> 00:31:53,431
What do I do?

534
00:31:54,371 --> 00:31:55,841
How am I going to handle this?

535
00:32:06,581 --> 00:32:08,181
Honey, it's me.

536
00:32:15,191 --> 00:32:16,191
Here.

537
00:32:18,761 --> 00:32:21,301
Review the Night Market Project Plan
as soon as you can.

538
00:32:22,231 --> 00:32:24,531
Wow, you're done already?

539
00:32:25,371 --> 00:32:29,601
- But...
- And Onjeong Fire Station called.

540
00:32:30,041 --> 00:32:33,171
They'll add CPR training
to the safety session this time.

541
00:32:33,911 --> 00:32:35,181
Right. Okay.

542
00:32:36,181 --> 00:32:37,211
But...

543
00:32:37,951 --> 00:32:39,981
How's your wife doing? Is she okay?

544
00:32:41,451 --> 00:32:42,481
How could she be okay?

545
00:32:43,151 --> 00:32:44,921
Not after being humiliated
in front of the whole country.

546
00:32:45,321 --> 00:32:47,191
Right. Of course.

547
00:32:48,191 --> 00:32:51,561
Anyway,
who on earth posted that video?

548
00:32:52,361 --> 00:32:56,101
What does it matter who posted it?
The damage is already done.

549
00:32:57,301 --> 00:32:59,201
She can't even bring herself
to leave the house right now.

550
00:33:00,331 --> 00:33:02,841
At this rate, I fear
she'll become socially anxious.

551
00:33:04,471 --> 00:33:06,511
Anyway, I'm sorry.

552
00:33:07,141 --> 00:33:10,041
It's all my fault, really.

553
00:33:11,381 --> 00:33:12,681
If we're going to assign blame,

554
00:33:13,451 --> 00:33:15,721
then it's my fault
for not teaching you better.

555
00:33:17,081 --> 00:33:20,521
Hey, anyway,
please tell her I'm really sorry.

556
00:33:20,961 --> 00:33:24,461
My daughter didn't do it on purpose.
She really didn't.

557
00:33:25,761 --> 00:33:26,761
I know.

558
00:33:28,861 --> 00:33:29,861
I should get going.

559
00:33:31,231 --> 00:33:33,001
Yes. Okay.

560
00:33:42,611 --> 00:33:44,281
Are you making mugwort soup?

561
00:33:44,781 --> 00:33:46,581
Wow, that smells incredible.

562
00:33:47,211 --> 00:33:49,821
Hey, what about Ju Ah?
Have you heard from her?

563
00:33:50,281 --> 00:33:53,921
I thought you said she was fine.
Come on, I'm sure she's okay.

564
00:33:53,991 --> 00:33:57,461
That's just what she's saying.
Imagine how upset she must be.

565
00:33:57,731 --> 00:33:59,291
- I'm home.
- I'm home.

566
00:33:59,361 --> 00:34:01,431
- My goodness.
- Oh, yes.

567
00:34:01,931 --> 00:34:04,601
- Wait, did you two come together?
- No, we just met on the way here.

568
00:34:05,071 --> 00:34:06,371
Whatever.

569
00:34:06,801 --> 00:34:09,841
She has to stay home
until her disciplinary hearing.

570
00:34:10,041 --> 00:34:12,741
- What? A disciplinary hearing?
- A hearing?

571
00:34:12,771 --> 00:34:15,611
Goodness, Mom, seriously!
Why did you have to say that?

572
00:34:15,811 --> 00:34:18,111
What, you want me to lie?
You had nowhere else to go today.

573
00:34:18,181 --> 00:34:21,521
You hung out at my clinic all day.
Where will you go tomorrow?

574
00:34:21,721 --> 00:34:23,921
Are you going to wander around
spas and parks all day?

575
00:34:24,351 --> 00:34:26,521
I can just say I'm on vacation
and stay home.

576
00:34:26,621 --> 00:34:29,891
Please.
Think the family will believe that?

577
00:34:30,491 --> 00:34:34,461
Gosh, still...
Mom, you're the worst!

578
00:34:35,231 --> 00:34:36,231
Hey, now...

579
00:34:37,061 --> 00:34:41,901
Wait. A disciplinary hearing?
But Ju Ah didn't do anything wrong.

580
00:34:42,501 --> 00:34:44,441
From the company's point of view,
it makes sense.

581
00:34:44,741 --> 00:34:47,141
It's not a big deal,
so please don't worry.

582
00:34:48,041 --> 00:34:51,311
So what did Dr. Yang say
when you apologized?

583
00:34:52,311 --> 00:34:55,881
He didn't really say anything.
I thought he'd push "Human Theater."

584
00:34:56,221 --> 00:34:59,391
- And he didn't say a word about it?
- No.

585
00:34:59,851 --> 00:35:01,391
If he'd brought it up,
I was just going to...

586
00:35:01,661 --> 00:35:04,431
pretend to give in
and agree to do "Human Theater."

587
00:35:05,161 --> 00:35:08,761
Then you should have just offered
to do it.

588
00:35:08,931 --> 00:35:11,901
No. Doing that would make it seem
like we were admitting our fault...

589
00:35:11,971 --> 00:35:13,801
and that this is the price
we have to pay.

590
00:35:14,001 --> 00:35:17,371
Yes, exactly. That's why
I couldn't bring it up first, see?

591
00:35:17,471 --> 00:35:19,841
It would have been like admitting
that Ju Ah pushed her on purpose.

592
00:35:19,911 --> 00:35:23,411
Goodness, you two overthink so much,
don't you?

593
00:35:24,051 --> 00:35:27,721
- Go on and get changed. Let's eat.
- Okay.

594
00:35:30,521 --> 00:35:32,351
That's strange, though.

595
00:35:32,651 --> 00:35:35,361
After he went to all that trouble
pestering us,

596
00:35:35,621 --> 00:35:36,761
why is he so quiet about it now?

597
00:35:37,021 --> 00:35:38,031
I know, right?

598
00:35:38,531 --> 00:35:40,831
I'm telling you,
the whole thing felt really strange.

599
00:35:45,601 --> 00:35:46,931
But that jerk, Gong Jeong Han...

600
00:35:47,771 --> 00:35:49,541
What if he never brings it up?

601
00:35:50,441 --> 00:35:53,241
I've got it all figured out.
Just trust me.

602
00:35:53,711 --> 00:35:54,711
All right, I get it.

603
00:35:55,211 --> 00:35:57,281
But why on earth are you telling me
not to say anything?

604
00:35:57,981 --> 00:36:01,051
Gong Jeong Han looked so guilty
and didn't know what to do.

605
00:36:01,481 --> 00:36:03,121
Isn't now the perfect time
to bring it up?

606
00:36:03,821 --> 00:36:06,621
If we jump at this chance
and ask him to be on the show,

607
00:36:07,051 --> 00:36:09,921
Dr. Han Seong Mi will realize
we staged the whole thing.

608
00:36:11,061 --> 00:36:13,061
What if this was all staged?

609
00:36:13,361 --> 00:36:18,201
- Mom, you're saying crazy things.
- Come on.

610
00:36:18,371 --> 00:36:21,871
Seriously, who would post a video
of themselves falling?

611
00:36:22,541 --> 00:36:23,901
What do you think?

612
00:36:24,571 --> 00:36:29,241
From the video's position and angle,
it was filmed from where we were.

613
00:36:29,411 --> 00:36:32,211
And Bucket was filming that day,
remember?

614
00:36:33,481 --> 00:36:38,321
- I don't know...
- Mom, tons of people were filming.

615
00:36:39,191 --> 00:36:40,991
So what you're saying is...

616
00:36:41,361 --> 00:36:46,191
she posted the video herself
to make us feel guilty?

617
00:36:46,361 --> 00:36:49,401
Exactly. That's the whole point
of staging something like this.

618
00:36:49,761 --> 00:36:52,831
You play on people's sympathy
to get what you want.

619
00:36:53,201 --> 00:36:55,771
What are you two even talking about?

620
00:36:56,871 --> 00:36:59,741
But then,
why didn't he say anything?

621
00:36:59,971 --> 00:37:03,111
Because it would be too obvious
if he brought it up right away.

622
00:37:03,211 --> 00:37:06,811
My gosh! That actually makes sense!
You're like a detective!

623
00:37:08,081 --> 00:37:12,721
You two are perfectly in sync.
Grandma, please stop them.

624
00:37:13,491 --> 00:37:17,291
All right, even I think you're going
a little too far with this.

625
00:37:17,391 --> 00:37:20,331
Mother, I wouldn't put it past her.

626
00:37:20,631 --> 00:37:23,401
Remember that picture she posted
of Director Song and me?

627
00:37:24,201 --> 00:37:28,601
She's the kind of woman
who would do anything for Bucket.

628
00:37:28,701 --> 00:37:31,271
Stop with the crazy talk.

629
00:37:31,511 --> 00:37:33,771
The whole company is in an uproar
over this.

630
00:37:33,971 --> 00:37:36,481
If this goes wrong,
Director Yang could get hurt too.

631
00:37:36,541 --> 00:37:38,381
That's true.

632
00:37:38,611 --> 00:37:42,051
Why would she knowingly do something
to put her own son in a bind?

633
00:37:42,151 --> 00:37:45,621
That's a good point too.

634
00:37:46,021 --> 00:37:48,791
She probably didn't realize
it would blow up like this.

635
00:37:49,121 --> 00:37:53,461
Simple-minded folks are shortsighted
and end up causing huge problems.

636
00:37:53,931 --> 00:37:56,731
My goodness.
Stop it, both of you. Let's eat.

637
00:37:57,001 --> 00:37:59,731
Don't assume the worst of people
based on speculation, all right?

638
00:38:00,271 --> 00:38:01,541
All right.

639
00:38:02,841 --> 00:38:03,841
Hey.

640
00:38:03,841 --> 00:38:06,711
Honestly, I think Director Yang
won't have an easy time marrying.

641
00:38:07,481 --> 00:38:09,411
Where did that come from
all of a sudden?

642
00:38:09,581 --> 00:38:13,851
I just remembered how giddy she was,
thinking he was marrying an heiress.

643
00:38:14,221 --> 00:38:15,281
Exactly! You know?

644
00:38:15,521 --> 00:38:19,321
A normal daughter-in-law
wouldn't be good enough, right?

645
00:38:20,351 --> 00:38:22,321
Since her son lived abroad
for so long,

646
00:38:22,721 --> 00:38:25,561
would she want him to live
with the family after marriage?

647
00:38:25,561 --> 00:38:26,791
Yes, I'm sure.

648
00:38:27,191 --> 00:38:30,731
Goodness, can you imagine how much
she'd torture her daughter-in-law?

649
00:38:31,171 --> 00:38:35,141
She thinks a woman's place is
at home, supporting her husband.

650
00:38:35,541 --> 00:38:37,401
And on top of that,
the family is huge!

651
00:38:37,811 --> 00:38:40,211
There's a divorced aunt
and a sister-in-law, too.

652
00:38:41,581 --> 00:38:44,951
Gong Ju Ah, could you imagine
marrying into a family like that?

653
00:38:45,281 --> 00:38:47,481
What? Why are you asking me?

654
00:38:47,651 --> 00:38:52,151
The gates of doom would swing open
right after your honeymoon.

655
00:38:52,721 --> 00:38:54,961
Gosh, it's horrifying
just to imagine.

656
00:38:55,591 --> 00:38:57,661
Why are you even imagining that,
Mom?

657
00:38:58,731 --> 00:39:00,331
Unbelievable.

658
00:39:06,331 --> 00:39:09,541
Goodness, she's so weird. I try
to cut her some slack, but I can't.

659
00:39:09,871 --> 00:39:12,511
Why is she flipping out
and imagining my honeymoon?

660
00:39:20,051 --> 00:39:21,051
Princess.

661
00:39:21,321 --> 00:39:25,251
It's such a shame the honeymoon's
already over, isn't it?

662
00:39:25,791 --> 00:39:29,591
Yes. Morning snorkeling
in the Maldives with my Bin...

663
00:39:29,661 --> 00:39:31,291
and sharing that glass of mojito.

664
00:39:33,191 --> 00:39:35,201
It all felt like a dream.

665
00:39:39,731 --> 00:39:42,601
Then how about we come back
for our babymoon?

666
00:39:43,401 --> 00:39:45,311
Stop.

667
00:39:47,111 --> 00:39:49,281
Everyone must be waiting.
We should hurry inside.

668
00:39:51,611 --> 00:39:55,521
Thank you so much, Princess.
For agreeing to live with my family.

669
00:39:56,151 --> 00:39:58,021
Of course, I would.

670
00:39:58,351 --> 00:40:02,621
You lived abroad for so long, Bin.
You must have missed your family.

671
00:40:03,221 --> 00:40:05,791
It'll be nice and lively
with everyone under one roof.

672
00:40:06,661 --> 00:40:07,731
My princess...

673
00:40:08,301 --> 00:40:10,831
How can you be so kindhearted?

674
00:40:16,171 --> 00:40:17,201
My goodness.

675
00:40:17,841 --> 00:40:20,511
Who cares? It's fun to imagine.

676
00:40:22,181 --> 00:40:25,611
Goodness, can you imagine how much
she'd torture her daughter-in-law?

677
00:40:26,351 --> 00:40:30,581
She thinks a woman's place is
at home, supporting her husband.

678
00:40:31,191 --> 00:40:33,051
And on top of that,
the family is huge!

679
00:40:33,421 --> 00:40:35,791
There's a divorced aunt
and a sister-in-law, too.

680
00:40:37,391 --> 00:40:39,961
No!

681
00:40:42,261 --> 00:40:45,471
Family events, cooking, housework...
Seriously,

682
00:40:45,571 --> 00:40:48,201
she's someone
who handles everything perfectly.

683
00:40:52,011 --> 00:40:56,941
But I'm terrible at all that stuff.
What am I going to do?

684
00:41:00,981 --> 00:41:02,221
Just lovely.

685
00:41:07,091 --> 00:41:09,161
We're back from our honeymoon.

686
00:41:09,891 --> 00:41:13,091
We're back,
Grandfather, Father, Mother.

687
00:41:13,091 --> 00:41:14,831
Yes, welcome back.

688
00:41:15,431 --> 00:41:16,931
You two must be tired.
Go and get some rest.

689
00:41:17,801 --> 00:41:18,801
So where are the presents?

690
00:41:19,101 --> 00:41:21,641
- You did get us some, right?
- Of course, we did.

691
00:41:24,371 --> 00:41:25,371
Good.

692
00:41:38,691 --> 00:41:43,461
Welcome to the world of in-laws.
That's the Yang family calendar.

693
00:41:43,521 --> 00:41:44,691
Memorize it by the end of the day.

694
00:41:45,131 --> 00:41:46,391
Eight ancestral rites a year.

695
00:41:46,391 --> 00:41:48,531
Weekends are for seasonal outings
or hiking trips.

696
00:41:48,761 --> 00:41:50,501
And don't forget the foodie tours.

697
00:41:50,761 --> 00:41:54,571
Mom, she's part of the family now.
You should tell her the rules.

698
00:41:54,941 --> 00:41:58,741
Speak softly. Don't show your gums.
Wear subtle makeup. Dress modestly.

699
00:41:58,811 --> 00:42:02,281
- And keep your hair neat. Got it?
- Yes, Mother.

700
00:42:02,481 --> 00:42:06,251
Order me hypoallergenic wet wipes
and premium intensive body lotion.

701
00:42:06,551 --> 00:42:07,651
Yes, Aunt.

702
00:42:07,711 --> 00:42:10,981
A new Riomere necklace, isn't it?
I'll be wearing it tomorrow.

703
00:42:11,291 --> 00:42:12,651
Oh, sure thing, Eun Bin.

704
00:42:13,021 --> 00:42:15,261
All right, then.
Let's see your cooking skills.

705
00:42:15,791 --> 00:42:16,791
Right now?

706
00:42:17,091 --> 00:42:18,091
What, did you think
I meant tomorrow?

707
00:42:21,961 --> 00:42:26,071
Meals are at 7 a.m., 1 p.m.,
and 7 p.m. sharp.

708
00:42:26,531 --> 00:42:30,001
A meal has multigrain rice, veggies,
white fish, meat, and a soup.

709
00:42:30,441 --> 00:42:31,441
Yes, Mother.

710
00:42:31,511 --> 00:42:34,811
We make soy sauce and pastes,
persimmon vinegar, and plum syrup.

711
00:42:34,941 --> 00:42:37,281
We make fresh kimchi weekly,
along with many pickles,

712
00:42:37,281 --> 00:42:38,511
and prepare 200 cabbages
for winter kimchi.

713
00:42:39,011 --> 00:42:40,011
Yes, Mother.

714
00:42:40,811 --> 00:42:44,221
Cleaning is a ritual
to rid the house of stale energy.

715
00:42:44,451 --> 00:42:48,321
The entryway is an energy channel.
Keep it spotless at all times.

716
00:42:49,321 --> 00:42:50,321
Yes, Mother.

717
00:42:50,921 --> 00:42:52,791
Use only unscented disinfectant.

718
00:42:52,791 --> 00:42:53,891
The doorknobs
up to the second floor...

719
00:42:53,961 --> 00:42:55,761
must all be disinfected
morning and night.

720
00:42:56,431 --> 00:42:57,431
Yes, Mother.

721
00:42:57,871 --> 00:42:58,871
Harder.

722
00:42:59,531 --> 00:43:02,301
- Yes, Mother.
- Harder.

723
00:43:04,741 --> 00:43:07,471
Don't just dust what you can see.
Get into every last nook and cranny.

724
00:43:08,181 --> 00:43:11,451
- Yes, Mother.
- Don't you slack off in her room.

725
00:43:11,581 --> 00:43:14,981
- Yes, Mother.
- Use your fingers to feel for dust.

726
00:43:17,251 --> 00:43:18,251
Yes, Mother.

727
00:43:19,721 --> 00:43:20,721
Harder.

728
00:43:21,661 --> 00:43:23,621
- Yes, Mother.
- Harder!

729
00:43:23,721 --> 00:43:24,731
Yes, Mother!

730
00:43:26,431 --> 00:43:28,701
I can't do it.
There's no way I can do it.

731
00:43:29,131 --> 00:43:30,231
Seriously.

732
00:43:30,931 --> 00:43:34,171
Why did Mom put that in my head?
I'm totally scared now.

733
00:43:34,231 --> 00:43:35,771
Seriously.

734
00:43:45,051 --> 00:43:46,411
(Director Yang Hyun Bin)

735
00:43:46,911 --> 00:43:47,921
My gosh...

736
00:43:50,421 --> 00:43:51,591
What's with that look on your face?

737
00:43:52,221 --> 00:43:53,791
You look like
you're staring daggers at me.

738
00:43:54,321 --> 00:43:58,291
If we get married,
do I have to live with your parents?

739
00:43:58,661 --> 00:43:59,861
Where is this coming from?

740
00:44:00,191 --> 00:44:01,261
Answer me. Now.

741
00:44:03,461 --> 00:44:05,871
I haven't really thought about it.

742
00:44:06,531 --> 00:44:08,771
I've never lived with my family,
so...

743
00:44:09,101 --> 00:44:11,271
even just staying over on weekends
feels a little awkward.

744
00:44:12,411 --> 00:44:13,471
So that's a no, right?

745
00:44:14,311 --> 00:44:16,681
My parents don't have a spare room,
just a storage room.

746
00:44:17,241 --> 00:44:18,811
The room my aunt is using
was originally my room.

747
00:44:20,211 --> 00:44:21,221
Okay.

748
00:44:21,551 --> 00:44:22,651
Any more questions?

749
00:44:23,181 --> 00:44:24,451
That's all for today.

750
00:44:27,651 --> 00:44:29,291
What? Why are you laughing?

751
00:44:30,391 --> 00:44:31,391
No, it's just...

752
00:44:32,661 --> 00:44:36,701
I couldn't focus on work all day,
worrying that you might be upset.

753
00:44:36,961 --> 00:44:39,031
But here you were,
worrying about something so random.

754
00:44:39,371 --> 00:44:40,701
It's just a relief,
and kind of cute.

755
00:44:41,901 --> 00:44:42,901
Whatever.

756
00:44:44,301 --> 00:44:47,411
Did you go to your parents' house?
Did you give them what I asked?

757
00:44:48,041 --> 00:44:52,111
They didn't just throw it out
or something, did they?

758
00:44:52,351 --> 00:44:54,621
What are you talking about?
I told you, she's not like that.

759
00:44:54,921 --> 00:44:56,781
She was actually worried
about you getting disciplined.

760
00:44:57,351 --> 00:44:59,391
- Really?
- Yes, really.

761
00:45:00,521 --> 00:45:04,461
She must've had a long day.
And to think she worried about me.

762
00:45:04,661 --> 00:45:08,461
Yes. She was so worried about
how this would affect the company.

763
00:45:09,631 --> 00:45:10,631
That's a relief.

764
00:45:11,231 --> 00:45:12,231
So...

765
00:45:13,001 --> 00:45:14,701
why don't you come
and sit next to me?

766
00:45:15,101 --> 00:45:16,101
Honestly.

767
00:45:23,011 --> 00:45:24,011
What?

768
00:45:27,181 --> 00:45:29,381
What do we do?
It's too late to run away.

769
00:45:33,851 --> 00:45:35,691
- Hello, Mr. Gong.
- Uncle.

770
00:45:35,761 --> 00:45:36,761
Hey, Gong Ju Ah.

771
00:45:38,091 --> 00:45:39,261
What are you doing out here
this late...

772
00:45:40,531 --> 00:45:41,531
with a man?

773
00:45:41,931 --> 00:45:44,671
Uncle, come on. "A man?"

774
00:45:44,931 --> 00:45:46,431
He's the director at my company,
remember?

775
00:45:47,401 --> 00:45:49,871
Hello, Uncle Dae Han.
I'm Yang Hyun Bin.

776
00:45:50,741 --> 00:45:52,211
Yes, right.

777
00:45:53,071 --> 00:45:56,041
Wait, but why are you two
here together?

778
00:45:56,281 --> 00:45:59,011
Why do you think?
Something came up at work.

779
00:45:59,411 --> 00:46:01,751
Yes. It involves
my stepmother as well.

780
00:46:02,421 --> 00:46:03,951
Right!

781
00:46:04,551 --> 00:46:06,721
Right. Of course.
For a second there, I thought...

782
00:46:08,921 --> 00:46:13,061
Still, you two shouldn't be so close
like this around the neighborhood.

783
00:46:13,131 --> 00:46:15,861
- Got it?
- Yes, sir.

784
00:46:16,561 --> 00:46:19,401
Are you two done talking?
Let's go, Ju Ah.

785
00:46:19,671 --> 00:46:22,201
Director, I should head home now.

786
00:46:22,271 --> 00:46:25,071
Yes, Ms. Gong. See you at the office
the day after tomorrow. Head on in.

787
00:46:25,071 --> 00:46:26,271
About your stepmother.

788
00:46:27,841 --> 00:46:29,711
Our Ju Ah didn't push her
on purpose.

789
00:46:32,181 --> 00:46:33,181
I know that.

790
00:46:33,851 --> 00:46:36,881
Even if your stepmother
did hit my sister-in-law,

791
00:46:38,691 --> 00:46:39,821
our Gong Ju Ah...

792
00:46:41,021 --> 00:46:43,061
is not the type of person
to seek revenge.

793
00:46:43,491 --> 00:46:46,091
Of course not.
I would never think that.

794
00:46:46,861 --> 00:46:48,161
Uncle, have you been drinking?

795
00:46:49,561 --> 00:46:50,661
I had a little to drink.

796
00:46:51,231 --> 00:46:52,471
- Uncle! My gosh, careful.
- Oh, no.

797
00:46:52,731 --> 00:46:54,601
- Here, let me help him.
- Well...

798
00:46:55,371 --> 00:46:59,011
No. I'm fine.
I'm not that drunk. I'm fine.

799
00:46:59,741 --> 00:47:02,541
Stay away from our Ju Ah.

800
00:47:03,211 --> 00:47:04,851
Keep your distance. Got it?

801
00:47:05,351 --> 00:47:08,481
- Okay, I understand.
- Uncle, what's gotten into you?

802
00:47:08,481 --> 00:47:09,521
Okay, and another thing...

803
00:47:10,581 --> 00:47:13,491
That whole thing was an accident.
An accident, you hear?

804
00:47:13,821 --> 00:47:16,761
This talk about who's the assailant
and who's the victim,

805
00:47:16,921 --> 00:47:19,131
or saying we're protecting our own
or whatever. You hear me?

806
00:47:19,791 --> 00:47:21,401
- Pardon?
- That my brother...

807
00:47:21,401 --> 00:47:23,701
threw the match on purpose
or whatever...

808
00:47:24,931 --> 00:47:25,931
That kind of talk...

809
00:47:26,701 --> 00:47:28,501
That's not right, is it, Director?

810
00:47:29,041 --> 00:47:31,541
Uncle, who said that to you?

811
00:47:32,241 --> 00:47:33,241
Someone.

812
00:47:33,941 --> 00:47:36,311
A sharp-tongued, nasty woman.

813
00:47:37,241 --> 00:47:38,351
She thinks being pretty
is an excuse?

814
00:47:40,311 --> 00:47:41,311
But she really is pretty.

815
00:47:42,721 --> 00:47:43,921
- Well...
- What are you even talking about?

816
00:47:44,021 --> 00:47:45,721
No, I mean,
she's really pretty, but...

817
00:47:45,821 --> 00:47:48,321
- Seriously, what is wrong with you?
- No, it's just... She acts like...

818
00:47:49,291 --> 00:47:52,961
- Is it all about looks?
- For crying out loud.

819
00:47:53,591 --> 00:47:55,131
Good grief.

820
00:48:04,071 --> 00:48:07,641
Uncle, who were you drinking with?

821
00:48:08,011 --> 00:48:09,281
By myself.

822
00:48:09,641 --> 00:48:12,451
I was upset, so I had a bottle.
Only one bottle.

823
00:48:13,111 --> 00:48:16,381
Why were you drinking alone?
Because of the divorce?

824
00:48:16,451 --> 00:48:18,021
Or because you bombed the interview?

825
00:48:21,091 --> 00:48:22,091
Wrong!

826
00:48:22,861 --> 00:48:23,861
Wrong on both counts.

827
00:48:24,221 --> 00:48:26,361
Then why are you upset?

828
00:48:27,191 --> 00:48:28,201
Because of you.

829
00:48:29,001 --> 00:48:30,001
I got into a fight because of you.

830
00:48:30,361 --> 00:48:33,471
What? With who?
Who did you fight with over me?

831
00:48:34,301 --> 00:48:35,501
Someone... The...

832
00:48:36,701 --> 00:48:38,571
The woman whose hair smells so good.

833
00:48:38,971 --> 00:48:43,111
Wow, a woman already? You work fast.

834
00:48:44,341 --> 00:48:45,581
Hey,
are you just figuring that out now?

835
00:48:45,951 --> 00:48:48,751
Hey, the "Dae" in my name
stands for "great."

836
00:48:49,251 --> 00:48:52,291
- Really?
- Of course. I'm great.

837
00:48:52,351 --> 00:48:53,421
You are great.

838
00:48:53,791 --> 00:48:57,521
- Our Dae Han is great.
- Yes, my uncle is the best.

839
00:49:06,771 --> 00:49:08,801
Goodness, forget it!
I must have been crazy.

840
00:49:08,801 --> 00:49:10,341
I should've known better
than to hang out with you.

841
00:49:10,401 --> 00:49:12,241
Never contact me again, you hear?

842
00:49:12,541 --> 00:49:14,671
Hey, Dong Suk! Hey!

843
00:49:23,521 --> 00:49:25,851
I'm sorry for being so mean earlier.

844
00:49:26,591 --> 00:49:27,651
What I said at the end...

845
00:49:28,461 --> 00:49:29,461
I take it back.

846
00:49:31,121 --> 00:49:32,291
(I'm sorry
for being so mean earlier.)

847
00:49:32,391 --> 00:49:33,431
(What I said at the end...
I take it back.)

848
00:49:35,201 --> 00:49:36,201
Mom.

849
00:49:36,731 --> 00:49:39,301
- What?
- Are you dating the clinic manager?

850
00:49:40,801 --> 00:49:41,801
What?

851
00:49:42,371 --> 00:49:44,941
No, what makes you say that?

852
00:49:45,741 --> 00:49:47,541
Dad called, and he was furious.

853
00:49:48,111 --> 00:49:49,781
He said you two were calling
each other "babe."

854
00:49:50,011 --> 00:49:52,911
What? Oh, that was...

855
00:49:53,481 --> 00:49:57,051
Mr. Gong and I went to court
and ran into them.

856
00:49:58,121 --> 00:50:02,091
The way your dad and that woman
acted was so infuriating, so...

857
00:50:02,121 --> 00:50:03,721
So you were just
putting on an act for Dad?

858
00:50:04,261 --> 00:50:06,091
Yes, of course.

859
00:50:10,331 --> 00:50:14,301
Mr. Gong didn't buy me this doll.
I won it from a claw machine.

860
00:50:14,571 --> 00:50:18,811
We went to an arcade
to celebrate our divorces.

861
00:50:19,611 --> 00:50:20,941
Mom, listen. I...

862
00:50:21,371 --> 00:50:23,081
I want to inherit the clinic
without any issues.

863
00:50:23,781 --> 00:50:25,811
Because I think
that's what you want.

864
00:50:26,251 --> 00:50:27,251
You're right.

865
00:50:28,051 --> 00:50:30,451
That's my goal in life.

866
00:50:30,821 --> 00:50:33,751
I'm all for you dating
or even getting remarried,

867
00:50:34,221 --> 00:50:36,291
and I know that
Mr. Gong is a good person, but...

868
00:50:38,631 --> 00:50:39,761
it can't be him.

869
00:50:40,461 --> 00:50:41,531
You know that, right?

870
00:50:42,861 --> 00:50:46,331
Yes. Do you even need to ask?
Absolutely not.

871
00:50:46,531 --> 00:50:49,841
And besides, I don't feel that way
about him at all.

872
00:50:51,201 --> 00:50:52,211
Okay.

873
00:50:53,441 --> 00:50:55,811
Don't worry about stuff like that,
and just study, son.

874
00:51:15,931 --> 00:51:17,601
What's the point of sending this?

875
00:51:21,601 --> 00:51:22,601
Dong Suk.

876
00:51:23,601 --> 00:51:25,641
I'm sorry for being
so petty earlier.

877
00:51:26,571 --> 00:51:29,311
And that last thing you said...

878
00:51:30,511 --> 00:51:31,751
I'll pretend I didn't hear it.

879
00:51:32,881 --> 00:51:34,581
Even if our families
hate each other,

880
00:51:35,251 --> 00:51:36,351
let's not be like that.

881
00:51:37,551 --> 00:51:39,651
Let it go and get some sleep.

882
00:51:40,891 --> 00:51:42,091
I'm sorry.

883
00:51:51,501 --> 00:51:52,771
Is she really mad at me?

884
00:52:25,571 --> 00:52:27,501
Why did she read it but not reply?

885
00:52:28,641 --> 00:52:30,071
Did she fall asleep, or what?

886
00:52:32,241 --> 00:52:33,311
Is it morning?

887
00:52:37,011 --> 00:52:39,411
Did I just fall asleep
waiting for her text?

888
00:52:40,251 --> 00:52:43,251
Man, Gong Dae Han,
you've really lost your mind.

889
00:52:43,481 --> 00:52:46,791
Goodness. Hey, are you still asleep?

890
00:52:47,791 --> 00:52:50,921
What were you doing
out drinking so late, man?

891
00:52:51,321 --> 00:52:54,461
Get up and help Mom
and your sister-in-law, you punk.

892
00:52:54,591 --> 00:52:55,661
Goodness.

893
00:52:56,201 --> 00:52:57,361
Hey, did you use my shampoo?

894
00:52:57,731 --> 00:52:59,871
Since when was there such a thing
as your shampoo?

895
00:53:00,471 --> 00:53:03,971
Are you serious?
I told you not to use it! It's mine!

896
00:53:04,201 --> 00:53:06,241
How many times did you use it?
How many pumps?

897
00:53:06,841 --> 00:53:08,111
My gosh, you're so petty.

898
00:53:08,411 --> 00:53:12,281
Hey, don't wear my clothes anymore.
And don't wear my socks either.

899
00:53:12,451 --> 00:53:15,051
You're one to talk. Don't be eyeing
the new underwear I bought.

900
00:53:16,081 --> 00:53:19,951
Look at you, talking back
to your big brother. Unbelievable.

901
00:53:21,691 --> 00:53:22,761
Don't you dare.

902
00:53:23,391 --> 00:53:25,431
You thought I'd stop
just because you said that?

903
00:53:25,791 --> 00:53:27,961
- Why, you...
- Stop it. Stop...

904
00:53:27,961 --> 00:53:30,101
- You little punk.
- Stop while I'm being nice.

905
00:53:30,161 --> 00:53:31,361
- You punk.
- Stop it.

906
00:53:31,431 --> 00:53:33,031
- Oh, dear.
- I said, stop!

907
00:53:33,101 --> 00:53:34,631
There they go again,
first thing in the morning.

908
00:53:34,701 --> 00:53:39,111
I never dreamed they'd still
be acting like this in their 50s.

909
00:53:39,771 --> 00:53:41,611
That's how brothers are.

910
00:53:42,111 --> 00:53:46,611
Always competing, always making up.
A cycle they repeat all their lives.

911
00:53:46,951 --> 00:53:50,281
Bickering like that is a sign
of their emotional closeness,

912
00:53:50,351 --> 00:53:54,051
so just think of it as raising
two elementary schoolers...

913
00:53:54,121 --> 00:53:57,121
- your whole life.
- No, thank you. I can't.

914
00:53:57,261 --> 00:53:59,461
- I'm so sick of it.
- Mom!

915
00:53:59,531 --> 00:54:01,691
- Hey, get back here!
- Mom! He keeps bugging me!

916
00:54:01,731 --> 00:54:03,661
- Hey, you...
- Seong Mi! He's picking on me!

917
00:54:03,861 --> 00:54:04,861
- Stop it.
- Honestly.

918
00:54:04,931 --> 00:54:07,201
This little pipsqueak
is getting fresh with me.

919
00:54:07,401 --> 00:54:10,741
- Why do you always pick on Dae Han?
- Honestly.

920
00:54:11,171 --> 00:54:14,641
- See? Told you so. Oh, man.
- Why, you little...

921
00:54:14,841 --> 00:54:15,881
That's enough!

922
00:54:16,481 --> 00:54:18,311
Do you two want to stand
in the corner all morning...

923
00:54:18,681 --> 00:54:19,911
or sit in a time-out?

924
00:54:20,481 --> 00:54:21,581
- No, ma'am.
- No, ma'am.

925
00:54:22,821 --> 00:54:26,051
- Goodness.
- Is this it? Where is everyone?

926
00:54:26,551 --> 00:54:30,361
You really don't know a thing
about your own house.

927
00:54:30,421 --> 00:54:34,261
Woo Jae got off his part-time job
late last night,

928
00:54:34,331 --> 00:54:35,401
so he's sleeping in.

929
00:54:35,701 --> 00:54:37,431
And Ju Ah
doesn't have to work today,

930
00:54:37,701 --> 00:54:40,371
so she's sleeping in for once.
Don't you know anything?

931
00:54:40,431 --> 00:54:42,871
Oh, well... This kid.

932
00:54:43,171 --> 00:54:45,211
Where are you going? Look at him.

933
00:54:45,411 --> 00:54:48,981
He's leaving without helping, Mom.
He always tries to get out of work.

934
00:54:49,041 --> 00:54:50,041
Hey!

935
00:54:50,311 --> 00:54:52,181
No matter how old you get,
he's still your older brother.

936
00:54:52,481 --> 00:54:53,551
Don't be so disrespectful.

937
00:54:53,611 --> 00:54:55,981
No, that's not it, Mom.
This is so unfair.

938
00:54:56,421 --> 00:54:57,651
If I'm born again in my next life,

939
00:54:58,251 --> 00:55:00,791
I hope I'm born just one minute,
even one second, before he is.

940
00:55:01,351 --> 00:55:02,721
- Good grief.
- Just get inside.

941
00:55:04,121 --> 00:55:05,291
Unbelievable.

942
00:55:09,901 --> 00:55:13,671
Now, where was Ju Ah's room?
This one?

943
00:55:14,471 --> 00:55:17,971
- This one. My gosh, you scared me!
- Man, you scared me.

944
00:55:18,941 --> 00:55:20,541
Dad, what are you doing here?

945
00:55:21,211 --> 00:55:22,811
What are you doing
coming out of your sister's room?

946
00:55:23,341 --> 00:55:25,711
Dad, we switched rooms ages ago.

947
00:55:26,111 --> 00:55:27,811
You did? When was that?

948
00:55:28,081 --> 00:55:30,221
When I was a high school sophomore.
Ten years ago.

949
00:55:31,181 --> 00:55:33,991
Really? How can I remember
something from ten years ago?

950
00:55:34,691 --> 00:55:35,721
I guess we did.

951
00:55:39,461 --> 00:55:42,101
It feels so good not having to work.

952
00:55:43,461 --> 00:55:47,731
I don't have to watch what I say
or worry about what to wear to work.

953
00:55:47,801 --> 00:55:49,401
And I don't have to get on
a packed rush hour train.

954
00:55:53,341 --> 00:55:57,081
Of course,
I miss you like crazy too.

955
00:56:01,011 --> 00:56:02,521
What? What's wrong?

956
00:56:02,851 --> 00:56:04,951
You scared me! Wait...

957
00:56:05,121 --> 00:56:08,021
Dad, what are you doing in my room?
Why didn't you knock?

958
00:56:08,421 --> 00:56:10,261
I did knock.
You just didn't hear me.

959
00:56:11,521 --> 00:56:14,991
If you see I'm on the phone,
you should clear your throat.

960
00:56:15,361 --> 00:56:17,701
And what's with you?
Look at the state of you.

961
00:56:18,201 --> 00:56:19,231
What about me?

962
00:56:19,601 --> 00:56:23,901
Your hair and clothes are a mess.
You look like a total slob.

963
00:56:24,901 --> 00:56:27,371
What are you talking about?
I look amazing without makeup.

964
00:56:27,571 --> 00:56:31,711
This is how it's meant to look.
You don't know what vintage is?

965
00:56:32,451 --> 00:56:35,721
Vintage, my foot.
More like just plain old shabby.

966
00:56:35,921 --> 00:56:39,621
- It'd make a perfect cleaning rag.
- What? A rag?

967
00:56:43,361 --> 00:56:44,391
I'd love to see that.

968
00:56:44,791 --> 00:56:47,861
Gong Ju Ah with messy hair
and her flawless bare face.

969
00:56:50,461 --> 00:56:55,341
Your mother looks like a queen
even right after she wakes up,

970
00:56:55,641 --> 00:56:57,001
but what happened with you?

971
00:56:57,741 --> 00:57:01,371
Why are you picking on me so early?
Seriously, Dad, why are you in here?

972
00:57:01,771 --> 00:57:03,211
I was worried about you.

973
00:57:03,481 --> 00:57:05,411
I thought you'd be upset
that you couldn't go to work.

974
00:57:06,211 --> 00:57:08,251
Since when
have you ever cared so much?

975
00:57:08,821 --> 00:57:12,021
Are you really okay?
Is there anything I can do to help?

976
00:57:12,321 --> 00:57:13,621
What could you possibly do?

977
00:57:13,951 --> 00:57:16,591
It'll all blow over,
so don't worry about it.

978
00:57:16,921 --> 00:57:20,691
That's a relief.
I'll take your word for it and go.

979
00:57:21,031 --> 00:57:22,531
And don't come back.

980
00:57:23,061 --> 00:57:24,061
All right.

981
00:57:25,161 --> 00:57:26,171
Gong Ju Ah.

982
00:57:27,501 --> 00:57:28,531
By the way...

983
00:57:28,871 --> 00:57:31,071
When are you bringing your boyfriend
to meet us?

984
00:57:31,801 --> 00:57:34,771
Unbelievable.
How much did you overhear?

985
00:57:37,241 --> 00:57:40,111
"Of course,
I miss you like crazy too."

986
00:57:41,351 --> 00:57:42,421
This is so humiliating.

987
00:57:43,121 --> 00:57:44,181
Please just go.

988
00:57:44,781 --> 00:57:47,251
Don't you tell anyone in the family,
you hear me?

989
00:57:47,791 --> 00:57:49,121
All right.

990
00:57:49,661 --> 00:57:52,331
For the record, I'm all for it.

991
00:57:52,661 --> 00:57:55,031
I like that guy.

992
00:57:57,001 --> 00:57:58,731
- "I Miss you like crazy."
- Honestly...

993
00:57:59,371 --> 00:58:01,801
Wait, what is he talking about?
How would he even know who it is?

994
00:58:16,051 --> 00:58:17,251
What are you talking about?

995
00:58:17,821 --> 00:58:20,391
Why on earth are they considering
a harsher punishment for Gong Ju Ah?

996
00:58:20,721 --> 00:58:24,591
We handled the fallout and press.
So why?

997
00:58:25,191 --> 00:58:27,361
Director Baek has drawn his sword,

998
00:58:27,361 --> 00:58:28,831
so he's determined
to cut someone down.

999
00:58:29,431 --> 00:58:32,671
He's out to mar the Fashion Division
to prove he's on top.

1000
00:58:32,931 --> 00:58:36,341
Then he should be coming after me.
I'm the one in charge, so why Ju Ah?

1001
00:58:36,571 --> 00:58:38,171
Because she already has a record.

1002
00:58:38,701 --> 00:58:41,071
- What?
- The home shopping incident.

1003
00:58:41,911 --> 00:58:42,911
Strike two.

1004
00:58:45,811 --> 00:58:46,811
Darn it.

1005
00:58:47,951 --> 00:58:52,251
You know I fabricated that incident,
don't you, Director, Mr. Park?

1006
00:58:52,851 --> 00:58:55,221
To see Ms. Gong getting in trouble
for something I did...

1007
00:58:55,621 --> 00:58:56,861
is more than I can bear.

1008
00:58:57,661 --> 00:58:59,331
If you come forward with that now,

1009
00:58:59,561 --> 00:59:01,731
wouldn't that just make things
more complicated?

1010
00:59:05,161 --> 00:59:07,471
I should've just been fired
back then.

1011
00:59:08,471 --> 00:59:11,571
Hey, calm down.
We need to focus on a solution.

1012
00:59:12,241 --> 00:59:15,241
Then what's going to happen
to Ms. Gong?

1013
00:59:15,981 --> 00:59:17,841
We'll have to see what they decide,
but...

1014
00:59:18,581 --> 00:59:22,721
The consensus is, two PR incidents
in a row is a serious problem.

1015
00:59:24,251 --> 00:59:25,381
According to regulations,

1016
00:59:26,021 --> 00:59:28,391
if this is judged to be
a repeated offense...

1017
00:59:30,791 --> 00:59:32,631
Termination could even be
on the table.

1018
00:59:40,831 --> 00:59:41,831
Termination...

1019
00:59:42,871 --> 00:59:45,241
I really didn't see this coming.

1020
00:59:46,911 --> 00:59:51,041
The employees suffer from
the Taehan executives' conflict.

1021
00:59:51,641 --> 00:59:54,781
So they might fire me
to make an example out of me?

1022
00:59:54,911 --> 00:59:57,651
I won't let that happen.
You trust me, right?

1023
01:00:01,191 --> 01:00:03,521
So Hye must be really shaken up.

1024
01:00:04,121 --> 01:00:07,131
Yes. She wanted to confess
and hand in her resignation,

1025
01:00:07,191 --> 01:00:08,261
but I stopped her.

1026
01:00:08,691 --> 01:00:11,131
Good call. If she came forward now,

1027
01:00:11,201 --> 01:00:13,931
we'd both get fired
for covering it up.

1028
01:00:15,741 --> 01:00:19,741
Do you think Dr. Han could make it
to the hearing tomorrow?

1029
01:00:20,571 --> 01:00:24,341
I think it'd be good if Dr. Han
and a few VIPs who were there...

1030
01:00:24,411 --> 01:00:26,011
could testify about
what happened that day.

1031
01:00:29,181 --> 01:00:31,781
I'll talk to her about it.

1032
01:00:33,191 --> 01:00:37,261
I'm going home to ask my stepmother
to write a statement.

1033
01:00:38,061 --> 01:00:39,131
You think she'll write one?

1034
01:00:39,861 --> 01:00:42,401
Of course. She'll be happy to.

1035
01:00:48,271 --> 01:00:52,971
I'm not really sure
how to write a statement like that.

1036
01:00:53,541 --> 01:00:56,681
Don't worry, it's not hard.
You just have to write...

1037
01:00:56,741 --> 01:00:59,111
that you don't think
the incident was intentional.

1038
01:00:59,811 --> 01:01:03,351
Just write it out by hand,
take a photo, and send it to me.

1039
01:01:04,051 --> 01:01:07,291
Jeong Han's daughter...
To think she could get fired...

1040
01:01:08,121 --> 01:01:09,561
This situation
has really gotten out of hand.

1041
01:01:10,621 --> 01:01:14,961
I know. Gong Ju Ah
is in a really tough spot.

1042
01:01:15,391 --> 01:01:16,401
But...

1043
01:01:17,301 --> 01:01:20,831
could I
maybe think about it for a bit?

1044
01:01:21,671 --> 01:01:23,871
- What?
- Honey?

1045
01:01:24,471 --> 01:01:27,941
It's just that...
Honey, the way I felt...

1046
01:01:28,171 --> 01:01:32,511
I thought maybe, just a little,
it might have been intentional.

1047
01:01:37,081 --> 01:01:39,991
I can't lie about it.
Right, Hyun Bin?

1048
01:01:44,121 --> 01:01:45,121
Well...

1049
01:01:48,761 --> 01:01:49,761
Ju Ah.

1050
01:01:51,501 --> 01:01:53,031
What are you doing out here
all alone?

1051
01:01:53,731 --> 01:01:54,731
Mom.

1052
01:01:55,971 --> 01:01:57,471
What's wrong? What's going on?

1053
01:01:58,641 --> 01:02:00,671
I need your help.

1054
01:02:01,911 --> 01:02:04,941
What is it?
What can I do? Just tell me.

1055
01:02:10,681 --> 01:02:11,821
What do you think you're doing?

1056
01:02:12,791 --> 01:02:14,121
Are you really not going
to write that statement?

1057
01:02:15,121 --> 01:02:16,121
Honey.

1058
01:02:16,421 --> 01:02:19,991
If Jeong Han's daughter gets fired,
there's no going back for us.

1059
01:02:20,631 --> 01:02:21,631
Se Ri.

1060
01:02:21,991 --> 01:02:25,031
Don't tell me you're planning
to get your revenge this way.

1061
01:02:26,131 --> 01:02:28,931
What if Hyun Bin gets caught
in the crossfire?

1062
01:02:29,771 --> 01:02:32,171
How would Hyun Bin
possibly get hurt?

1063
01:02:32,741 --> 01:02:34,771
Even if Gong Ju Ah
ends up getting fired,

1064
01:02:35,571 --> 01:02:36,981
it's not like it's my fault.

1065
01:02:38,311 --> 01:02:39,451
Honey.

1066
01:02:51,691 --> 01:02:52,731
What about you, Mom?

1067
01:02:53,491 --> 01:02:55,731
Did everything go well in there?

1068
01:02:57,031 --> 01:02:59,071
Yes, I just told them what I saw.

1069
01:03:00,131 --> 01:03:02,371
But it was really tense in there.

1070
01:03:02,771 --> 01:03:05,141
What do you expect?
It's a huge corporation.

1071
01:03:08,371 --> 01:03:12,681
Well, thanks for coming.
I know you're busy.

1072
01:03:14,281 --> 01:03:17,021
Don't be silly. I'm your mother.

1073
01:03:18,221 --> 01:03:19,221
I'm sorry.

1074
01:03:32,401 --> 01:03:35,631
I guess his stepmother
didn't write the statement.

1075
01:03:35,841 --> 01:03:38,501
Of course not.
Would you, if you were her?

1076
01:03:39,711 --> 01:03:44,281
Poking her with the pin by mistake,
pushing her to save her...

1077
01:03:44,341 --> 01:03:45,851
She thinks you did it all
on purpose.

1078
01:03:47,681 --> 01:03:51,251
She'll probably think you did it
as revenge for what she did to me.

1079
01:03:51,881 --> 01:03:53,991
I didn't think she was like that.

1080
01:03:55,551 --> 01:03:57,661
What could possibly have given you
that idea?

1081
01:04:00,761 --> 01:04:01,831
The call cannot be...

1082
01:04:02,931 --> 01:04:03,931
She's not picking up?

1083
01:04:04,431 --> 01:04:06,601
No. What do we do now?

1084
01:04:06,731 --> 01:04:08,871
But her testimony is
the most important thing.

1085
01:04:09,901 --> 01:04:12,411
So it's true.
Your families are sworn enemies.

1086
01:04:13,441 --> 01:04:16,281
Even if she hates her, will she
just stand by and let her get fired?

1087
01:04:21,381 --> 01:04:24,551
If there are no other witnesses,
Ms. Gong Ju Ah, please come in.

1088
01:04:25,451 --> 01:04:28,521
- Hold on. Give us five minutes.
- It's okay, Director.

1089
01:04:29,121 --> 01:04:30,761
I'm going in.

1090
01:04:39,501 --> 01:04:40,571
Hold on a second.

1091
01:05:22,911 --> 01:05:25,541
(Recipe For Love)

1092
01:05:25,611 --> 01:05:27,811
I'm thinking about
using my stepmother's video.

1093
01:05:28,011 --> 01:05:29,751
I made things a bit more exciting,
didn't I?

1094
01:05:29,921 --> 01:05:32,821
I just want to see her
one last time before I die.

1095
01:05:33,051 --> 01:05:35,491
There's something
I absolutely have to tell her.

1096
01:05:35,891 --> 01:05:38,661
Let's sign the contract
for "Human Theater."

1097
01:05:38,721 --> 01:05:41,431
Cha Se Ri, she's a real genius.

1098
01:05:41,491 --> 01:05:44,501
This is so unexpected,
I'm actually a bit flustered.

1099
01:05:44,661 --> 01:05:46,371
You should have taken me with you.

1100
01:05:46,431 --> 01:05:49,201
This was a job for us old-timers.
Got it?

1101
01:05:49,871 --> 01:05:53,211
Meet me at the teahouse.
If you don't come, I'll come to you.

1102
01:05:54,272 --> 01:05:56,272
Dramaday.me
